<br>
Can they do better? Sure they can. No matter how good you are, there is always room for improvement. However, DAoC is a different game. I don't care what their CS is compared to EQ, other than for idle conversation. If I go and try DAoC and like it, then I'll be concerned about their CS. But I don't play a game based on their CS. Although, I might ultimately leave one because of their lack of CS. EQ's CS is definately in the comfort zone for me.<br>
<br>
Is DAoC going online a motivating factor to get EQ to try and improve their CS and content? Quite possibly, competition can be a healthy stimulous. I'm sure they are trying to stay in most people's &quot;comfort zone&quot;. But there is also a point of diminishing returns. I have NO doubt that DAoC will have very good CS for quite a while. They are going to trade CS for market share (translation: pour money into CS to keep people that try DAoC from leaving due to any problems that crop up).<br>
